HEADWORD: Damnableness
<hw>Dam"na*ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of
deserving damnation; execrableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>damnableness</qex> of this most execrable impiety.</q>
<rj><qau>Prynne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damnably</ent>⟦br⟧
